Former Big Brother Naija 2018 housemate, Lolu, has announced that his family just lost their brother-in-law to the deadly coronavirus disease. The reality show star made this known on his Twitter handle on Saturday, calling for prayers for his family. He said, ”About an hour ago, I lost my brother-in-law to Coronavirus. ”Please, remember our family in your prayers. Thank you.” Meanwhile, figures released by Johns Hopkins University indicated that there are nearly 1.7 million cases with a global death toll which has surpassed 100,000 and more than 370,000 recoveries. However, Nigeria now has 305 cases of coronavirus as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Friday confirmed seventeen new cases in the country. 